  "text": "R&D on export market shares, in a pure cross-section (for the year 1985), using a combination of OECD input−output tables and R&D statistics. He finds that indirect R&D from domestic sources appears to be more conducive to competitiveness than indirect R&D from abroad. [CITATION_1] examine the effect of national and international knowledge stocks for trade performance-calculated in a similar way to that of [CITATION_2] . However, while the authors find evidence of a positive impact from both types of spillovers, they do not discriminate between the two types, as they are included in separate estimations.",
